## Appendix B: Definitions and Glossary

| Term | Definition |
|---|---|
| AI Incident | Any event involving an AI system that causes or may cause harm, regulatory breach, data loss, or reputational damage |
| Eligible Data Breach | A data breach likely to result in serious harm to individuals (NDB scheme, Privacy Act Part IIIC) |
| Shadow AI | AI tools used by staff without organisational knowledge, approval, or oversight |
| Containment | Actions taken to limit the scope and impact of an incident |
| Eradication | Removing the root cause of an incident from the environment |
| NDB | Notifiable Data Breaches scheme — mandatory reporting of eligible data breaches to the OAIC |
| OAIC | Office of the Australian Information Commissioner — Australia's national privacy regulator |
| Statutory Tort | A civil cause of action for serious invasion of privacy (POLA Act 2024) — applies to ALL organisations |
| ACL | Australian Consumer Law — strict liability for misleading or deceptive conduct (s 18) |
| POLA Act | Privacy and Other Legislation Amendment Act 2024 |
| Tabletop Exercise | A discussion-based exercise simulating an incident scenario to test response procedures |
| ACSC | Australian Cyber Security Centre |
| RTO | Recovery Time Objective — the maximum acceptable time to restore operations |
| RPO | Recovery Point Objective — the maximum acceptable data loss measured in time |

